This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on March 29, 2013. The memorandum delegates the authority to appoint commissioned officers of the Ready Reserve Corps of the Public Health Service to the Secretary of Health and Human Services. It states that commissions issued under this authority cannot exceed a term of 6 months, except for certain programs that allow for longer terms. The memorandum also revokes a previous memorandum issued on May 31, 2011. The Secretary of Health and Human Services is directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.